    <h4>translate5 JIRA - report bugs and propose features</h4>
    <p>To report a bug or propose a feature, you need to log into <a href="http://jira.translate5.net/" target="_blank">translate5 JIRA</a>.</p>
    <p>If you want to report a bug, please be sure you really encountered a one. In case of any doubt, ask about it in <a href="https://groups.yahoo.com/neo/groups/translate5/info" target="_blank">translate5 Yahoo mailing list</a>.</p>
    <p>If you want to propose a feature, please be sure, your feature proposal is not already registered as a feature request in <a href="http://jira.translate5.net/" target="_blank">translate5 JIRA</a>. If it is already registered, please comment on the feature and/or vote for it.</p>
    <h4>Be part of the development</h4>
    <p>translate5 project is happy to have you as part of the development. Please write to <a href="mailto:support@translate5.net">support@translate5.net</a> and we will open an account in <a href="#source">translate5 code repository</a> for you.</p>
    <p><strong>The easiest way to contribute to translate5 development is to develop a translate5 plug-in, though.</strong> This can be done completely independent of translate5 core development. Plug-ins can be documented and uploaded to <a href="http://confluence.translate5.net/display/TPLO" target="_blank">translate5 plug-in directory</a>.</p>
    <p>How to develop a translate5 plug-in is documented in <a href="http://confluence.translate5.net/display/TAD" target="_blank">translate5 architecture documentation</a></p>
    <a name="source"></a><h4>translate5 source code</h4>
    <p>The current stable master branch of translate5 is <a href="https://bitbucket.org/mittagqi" target="_blank">published on bitbucket</a>.</p>
    <p>It is updated every night with the latest commits.</p>
    <p>For installation and update purposes we recommend the <a href="http://confluence.translate5.net/display/TIU" target="_blank">translate5 install &amp; update routines</a>, though. They build on packages provided by translate5 development team on a weekly basis.</p>
    
